event: message_saved
data: {"messageId":"lumk_FYGjoI8qXmOvficH","role":"user","content":"Simulate a production incident response workflow. Do ALL of these steps:\n\n1. Use incident_create to create a new P2 incident titled 'API Response Degradation - Elevated Latency' with description 'Users reporting slow chat responses, p99 latency above 10s threshold'\n\n2. Use incident_list to verify the incident was created\n\n3. Use prometheus_query to check actual API latency: query 'histogram_quantile(0.99, rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m]))' or a simpler query like 'up' to check service health\n\n4. Use loki_query to search for slow requests: query '{namespace=\"agentic-dev\",container=\"api\"} |= \"slow\" or \"timeout\"' for the last 30 minutes\n\n5. Use k8s_list_pods in namespace agentic-dev to check for any pod restarts or issues\n\n6. Use runbook_list to find available runbooks for diagnostics\n\n7. Use runbook_quick_diagnostics with the target service 'openagentic-api'\n\n8. Use incident_add_note to the incident with your diagnostic findings\n\n9. Use incident_resolve to resolve the incident with a summary of findings\n\nReport the full incident timeline with each action taken.","timestamp":"2026-02-20T21:57:32.377Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

